Fit Standardized Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated from a Multivariate Normal Distribution with Data Missing Not at Random - Structural Equation Modeling

Source: R/mvn_mnar_std_fit.sem.R
mvn_mnar_std_fit.sem.Rd

Fit Standardized Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated from a Multivariate Normal Distribution with Data Missing Not at Random - Structural Equation Modeling

mvn_mnar_std_fit.sem(data, taskid)

Arguments

data

n by 3 matrix or data frame. data[, 1] correspond to values for x. data[, 2] correspond to values for m. data[, 3] correspond to values for y.
taskid

Numeric. Task ID.

See also

Other model fit functions: fit.cov(), fit.ols(), fit.sem(), mvn_fit.ols_simulation_summary(), mvn_fit.ols_simulation(), mvn_fit.ols_task_summary(), mvn_fit.ols_task(), mvn_fit.ols(), mvn_mar_fit.sem_simulation_summary(), mvn_mar_fit.sem_simulation(), mvn_mar_fit.sem_task_summary(), mvn_mar_fit.sem_task(), mvn_mar_fit.sem(), mvn_mar_std_fit.sem_simulation_summary(), mvn_mar_std_fit.sem_simulation(), mvn_mar_std_fit.sem_task_summary(), mvn_mar_std_fit.sem_task(), mvn_mar_std_fit.sem(), mvn_mcar_fit.sem_simulation_summary(), mvn_mcar_fit.sem_simulation(), mvn_mcar_fit.sem_task_summary(), mvn_mcar_fit.sem_task(), mvn_mcar_fit.sem(), mvn_mcar_std_fit.sem_simulation_summary(), mvn_mcar_std_fit.sem_simulation(), mvn_mcar_std_fit.sem_task_summary(), mvn_mcar_std_fit.sem_task(), mvn_mcar_std_fit.sem(), mvn_mnar_fit.sem_simulation_summary(), mvn_mnar_fit.sem_simulation(), mvn_mnar_fit.sem_task_summary(), mvn_mnar_fit.sem_task(), mvn_mnar_fit.sem(), mvn_mnar_std_fit.sem_simulation_summary(), mvn_mnar_std_fit.sem_simulation(), mvn_mnar_std_fit.sem_task_summary(), mvn_mnar_std_fit.sem_task(), mvn_std_fit.sem_simulation_summary(), mvn_std_fit.sem_simulation(), mvn_std_fit.sem_task_summary(), mvn_std_fit.sem_task(), mvn_std_fit.sem()

Examples

taskid <- 1
data <- mvn_dat(taskid = taskid)
data <- mvn_dat_mnar(data = data, taskid = taskid)

# SEM with FIML -------------------------------------------------------------
mvn_mnar_std_fit.sem(data = data, taskid = taskid)
